                                                                                                                                     NATION BRIEFS
                   
	Washington, Jan. 1 (PTI): US authorities will not press criminal charges against 24-year-old Anu Solanki, who fled her house to escape an unhappy marriage, or Karan C. Jani, the 23-year-old man she drove off with. 
     
	But the authorities have not decided whether to move a civil court to get the duo to pay compensation for the $250,000 police spent searching for Solanki who was feared to have drowned. 
         
	Bangalore (PTI): Isro has launched a major initiative to provide satellite-based tele- education facilities to engineering colleges across the country in association with IIT Powai.
         
	Srinagar (PTI): A 22-year-old mentally challenged person, Rayees Ahmed Sheikh, was seriously injured when he stepped on a mine in Doornag Dandi forest in Anantnag district, police said on Tuesday. Rayees gave a slip to his family and ran into the forest.
         
	Bhopal (PTI): Uma Bharti was granted bail on Tuesday in a case of alleged insult to the national flag at a 2004 event here. Madhya Pradesh Congress general secretary Deepchand Yadav had moved court against the Bharatiya Janshakti Party president.
         
	Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A convict and an undertrial escaped on Monday night from the central jail here while being brought back from a court in Ernakulam, police said. Sunil Kumar, serving a one-and-a-half-year sentence, and Biju alias Karthik escaped after attacking their escorts.
         
	 Almora (PTI): A bear attacked a group of women in a forest near Dol village in Almora district on Monday, leaving two of them seriously injured, official sources said. The women were cutting grass in Sune forest.
                                                            
